From: Conan recipe maintainer
Subject: [PATCH] Silence -Wc++20-compat for the char8_t enum-class workaround

coda-oss defines `char8_t` as an `enum class` (legal in C++14/17) for
codebases that don't yet have C++20. Under gcc 10+, this triggers the
-Wc++20-compat warning, which becomes a hard error because coda-oss
adds -Werror via add_compile_options() — overriding any -Wno-error
flag passed in CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS.

Wrap the enum in a GCC diagnostic push/pop so the warning is suppressed
locally without disabling -Werror globally.

--- a/externals/coda-oss/modules/c++/coda_oss/include/coda_oss/string.h
+++ b/externals/coda-oss/modules/c++/coda_oss/include/coda_oss/string.h
@@ -54 +54,8 @@
-        enum class char8_t : unsigned char { }; // https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/types
+#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__)
+#pragma GCC diagnostic push
+#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wc++20-compat"
+#endif
+        enum class char8_t : unsigned char { }; // https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/types
+#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__)
+#pragma GCC diagnostic pop
+#endif